data.message:
Two small mistakes:
- You didn't add any layers.
- Wrapping every thing in a function is not really required.
Here's an updated version 
http://jsfiddle.net/AmrEldib/vnvxonqu/2/

thanks a lot, I usually use self-executing anonymous functions. so later I can pass whatever comes as a parameter to it.. 

and that layout thing.. it's different a bit of google maps terminology.. but I really like it..

does it have a limit quota like google's?
Sorry, does what have a limit quota?
Leaflet uses Mapbox for the tileLayer, is it totally free?

No, Mapbox is not free 
https://www.mapbox.com/plans/
But Leaflet doesn't only use Mapbox. It's an open library that works with (almost) all major map providers (Google, OpenStreetMap, Mapbox, Esri, OpenGeo, etc).
The layer I've added is an OpenStreetMap layer, not Mapbox
